```
# This is a .contextignore file for the 'getcontext' tool.
# It uses glob patterns, similar to a .gitignore file, to specify files
# and directories that should be excluded from the context export.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Common Directories to Ignore
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Python virtual environments and cache
__pycache__/
.venv/
venv/
env/
.mypy_cache/

# Node.js dependencies
node_modules/

# Build artifacts and distribution folders
build/
dist/
target/
out/

# Git directory
.git/

LICENSE


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# File Types to Ignore by Extension
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Log files
*.log

# Local database files
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# Temporary and swap files
*.tmp
*.swp

# Compiled Python files
*.pyc

# Asset files (not useful for code context)
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.gif
*.webp
*.ico
*.pdf
*.mp4


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Specific Files and Paths to Ignore
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Ignore specific configuration or credential files
local_settings.py
credentials.json
.env

# Ignore lock files for package managers
poetry.lock
package-lock.json

# Ignore a specific directory within your source code
src/getcontext/tests/data/

# Ignore all markdown files in the 'docs/internal' directory
docs/internal/*.md
```
getcontext*.txt
*.egg-info/
*__init__.py